==English==
===Adjective===
'''blootered'''
# [[drunk|Drunk]].
# {{rfv-sense}} exhausted (Scots and northern Irish)
 
===Quotations===
* '''1997,''' John Davies, ''Drugspeak'' [http://books.google.com/books?ie=UTF-8&hl=en&id=bEvKNWB3kOoC&pg=PA115&lpg=PA115&sig=RTBl3kS1gGpz38ezwHMGA81SS8I]
*: ''I found my drinking eased up when the all day drinking came in Scotland because although we all went mad on it at first, we were '''blootered''' every day, but after about 6 months you began to realise you could have a drink any time.''
* '''1999,''' Duncan McLean, ''Bucket of Tongues'' [http://books.google.com/books?ie=UTF-8&hl=en&id=0Z_1Mw7XgI4C&pg=PA92&lpg=PA92&sig=lX1ZkkRhyUU1eBJBQq4JTNGHx7g]
